‌Executive Summary‌


Computer Network Systems (CNS) is pleased to submit our proposal, in response to MENASCO MECH CONTRACTING LLC Request for Engineering Service on Demand – Mechanical BIM Modeller. CNS has an excellent track record of successfully designing solutions, transitioning, managing and operating ICT and networking solution, managed services and engineering services. We will bring to MENASCO MECH CONTRACTING LLC, our proven expertise, best practices, and deep industry experience that will capture and accelerate sustainable benefits.

We are excited about the opportunity and understand the strategic significance of this project to MENASCO MECH CONTRACTING LLC’s future success and we truly want to partner with you in this endeavor.

CNS is spread across the region with offices in Abu Dhabi, Dubai, Oman, KSA and Kuwait providing a holistic approach that covers all aspects of information communication technology system integration, consultancy, operation, managed services, and outsourcing. CNS also has state-of-the-art network operation centers in Abu Dhabi and Dubai that develop in-house software and applications providing end-to-end solutions to our customers and partners.

CNS will use the best practices in the industry to fulfil MENASCO MECH CONTRACTING LLC’s requirement taking into consideration the availability & the Quality of Service, the total cost of ownership and the return on investment (ROI). CNS has the experience, the expertise and a long history of providing superior quality, value, and reliable resources. CNS looks forward to working together with you and hopes that our solution and service offering is up to your requirements and expectations.

  2. ‌Confirmation & Deployment‌

    1. CNS has a professional service license to second staff to your offices.

    2. The service will start upon receiving a confirmed irrevocable LPO/Contract/Service Agreement.

    3. By issuing an LPO/Contract Agreement you are accepting all the terms and conditions of this proposal.

    4. Endorsement of a service contract between both companies is mandatory for labour inspection purposes. Two sets of originals will be endorsed, and each party will hold a set throughout the duration of service.

    5. If the service period extends over the specified LPO or Contract value, then the time sheets endorsed by your company will serve as proof of extension of service and all charges as per the prevailing agreement will be applicable for the additional service.

    6. In case the notice for demobilization is not given 15 days in advance as per our terms and conditions then the service will continue till the demobilization notice period is served and the same will be billed as per the approved timesheets.


  3. ‌Payment‌

    1. Monthly invoices should be settled within 30 days upon submission. Open credit is subject to Credit application approval from our service department.

    2. Monthly invoices will be submitted every calendar month supported with duly endorsed timesheet from MENASCO MECH CONTRACTING LLC.

    3. No further payment application or certification required for payment as we are providing time-based service and the unit of measurement of work is the endorsed timesheet from MENASCO MECH CONTRACTING LLC.

    4. All prices stated in our proposal is subject to any government fees, taxes or charge. VAT of 5% will apply as per the government regulation.

    5. If any charges are implemented by the government during the period of service or in future, such charges will be added to the value of this proposal from the date of its implementation by the government.

  4. ‌Timely Payment Settlement‌

    1. Any payment outstanding for more than 30 days may result in the demobilization of service without any prior notification.

    2. If de-mobilizing happens due to non-payment then CNS will be entitled to full payment for the service rendered till date and the minimum notice period of 15 days for demobilization as stipulated in the terms and conditions of this proposal.

    3. If CNS demobilizes the service due to non-payment of invoices by MENASCO MECH CONTRACTING LLC, then the responsibility of breaching the agreement is fully on MENASCO MECH CONTRACTING LLC and CNS will not be liable for any consequential damages arising out of the discontinuation of services.


  5. ‌Working hours and over time‌

    1. Our staff will adapt to your office or site timing as per the service authorization form endorsed at the start of each service.

    2. This fee proposal covers for up to 48 hours per week.

    3. The total working hours per week should not exceed 48 hours a week and more than 8 hours a day as per the labour law. This is excluding one hour lunch break. If your site or office timing does not facilitate 48 hours of working, this should not affect the weekly or monthly fees offered as per this proposal.

    4. If the service of our staff exceeds the 48 hours in a week and more than 8 hours in a day then the overtime rates would apply according to your approved time sheet.

    5. Unless otherwise stated in your LPO stating not to work over time, we do not need to obtain any written approval from you, other than the approved time sheets, to invoice the overtime.

    6. During the holy month of Ramadan the government stipulates a reduction of two hours in the regular working hours without any deduction in remuneration. Accordingly the reduced working hours cannot be pro rata reduced from our monthly fees or invoices. In case of hourly billing two hours will be added to the approved time sheet as per the government order.

    7. Over time rate will be applicable as below:


      Overtime Calculation per hour per staff


      OT calculation for a service with monthly fees of AED13000/- and working 48 hours/week.

      13000 /208(26x8) = 62.50 @1.25 = 78.00 normal days @1.5 = 94.00 for Sundays and Public Holidays


  6. ‌Non Hiring Clause‌

    By accepting our proposal MENASCO MECH CONTRACTING LLC undertakes not to recruit or hire directly or indirectly any of our staff for a minimum period of 2 years from date of finishing service with us. Please note that our staff are bound by NDA, not to join any of our customers for two years from the time they sever contract with CNS. In case if any such recruitment happens without the knowledge of MENASCO MECH CONTRACTING LLC, and if CNS brings to your notice of such violation, MENASCO MECH CONTRACTING LLC warrants to take immediate remedial actions to protect CNS’s business interests. CNS reserves the right to claim compensation if this clause is violated.

  7. ‌General Terms and Conditions‌


    1. The deployment lead-time varies from one day to 7 days depending on the staff availability. However, pre-deployment activities will be commence only after the paperwork is received and our finance department approve your credit limit.

    2. Currently we have staff readily available in the country to suit your deployment plan as discussed.


    3. The minimum notice period for terminating or extending an ongoing service of any staff is minimum

      (15) Fifteen days in advance. The last date of working will be considered 15 calendar days from the date of receipt of demobilization notice, in writing.


    4. Upon commencement of pre deployment process and testing & selection of staff is complete, the deployment should commence within 3 calendar days. For any delays from your side which warrants the reservation of the candidate for more than 3 days, billing will commence from the third day onwards.


    5. Evaluation or testing of staff on the job in your site office should be done within 3 working days.

    6. All necessary gate passes vehicle passes, site gears, PPE etc. required at site should be arranged by

      MENASCO MECH CONTRACTING LLC.

    7. Our staff is covered with general medical insurance and work man compensation insurance. Any other insurance which may be required on site will be the responsibility of MENASCO MECH CONTRACTING LLC.


    8. Deputed staff is entitled for 30 days paid leave in a calendar year as per labour law. We can postpone or prepone their leave as per your requirement. A suitable replacement will be provided to cover the leave period if his/her annual leave falls during the period of deputation as per this proposal.


    9. Computer workstations can be provided on lease basis. The workstation will remain the property of CNS and returned to CNS intact after the deputation is competed. Any damages or loss to the workstation or accessories while delivered to your premises will be the responsibility of MENASCO MECH CONTRACTING LLC.


    10. If the services are transferred from one emirate to another temporarily or permanently during the period of deputation, for any reasons, there will be a relocation charges of AED.500 per staff towards logistics arrangements. This will be applicable for each relocation request.


    11. If MENASCO MECH CONTRACTING LLC wishes to issue a temporary labour card for our staff or requires a police clearance certificate/ attestation/ PCR Tests/ medical fitness tests etc., the related charges should be reimbursed by MENASCO MECH CONTRACTING LLC.


    12. The validity of this proposal is for 30 days.
